### Linux Cheatsheet ###

## The directory structure ##

/bin 			binaries (Befehle)
/sbin 			sbin = System-Binaries / System Programs
/dev 			Development files
/boot 			Boot-Files / Bootloader

/cdrom 			CD-Rom contents (if inserted)
/media			USB sticks, external hard drives
/mnt 			External media are created

/etc 			Editable text configuration files, Cron-Jobs
/home 			Directory for users
/lib 			Libraries, Libraries for the operation of Linux
/lib64

/opt 			Manual installation of programs and configurations
/proc 			Running processes, are always created anew at system start
/run 			Information on current sessions

/root 			Admin directory
/srv 			Services & utilities
/sys 			System Folder / Kernel Interfaces
/tmp 			Temporary files
/usr 			Libraries of installed programs of external developers
/var 			Directories and files of programs such as Apache / Mail 
/var/log 		Log files (protocols)


## User & Groupes ##

root			System Root Group (Admin Permissions)
daemon			LLinux server & desktop services

# Creating a new user and adding him to a group
$ sudo adduser newUserName groupName

# Delete user
$ sudo deluser userName

# Remove user from group
$ sudo deluser userName groupName

# Create a new group
$ sudo addgroup newGroupName

# Edit Group Config File
$ sudo nano /etc/group
